what's an API?
An API is simply a set of rules that tells other programs how to communicate with your application.

/api/profile
these are API endpoints after api.

API methods:-
GET-to retrieve a journal
POST-to create a journal
DELETE-to delete a journal by id
PUT-to update a journal by id

Nodemon-automatically restarts your server whenever a change is detected
cors-it disables any other non trusted frontend website to read or peak data from your site's backend API and allows only trusted(set by you) websites to read or fetch data

why we use database?
-suppose we store journals once we start our server and make a journal entry it gets stored in RAM by default and when the server is restarted everything's gone cuz that was temporary so we need a database which has permanent memory

Mongoose
-by default we have to write complex commands to store data in mongodb so for easy access we use mongoose...
in brief words its a translator for mongodb

File work-
server.js-starts the server and loads other modules
.env-contains passwords, API keys and other security stuff that can't be revealed
.gitignore-files and directories that will be ignored when we push the project to github
db.js-connection to mongodb(async is used for mongo connection and await for waiting till mongo connects)
then we export this file to server.js

the schema files:-
controllers- contains main logic for journal posting and all....
models-contains what will be stored when a journal is created
routes-mapping of which function should be called on a request


